CREATED:20260302T145016Z
DESCRIPTION:SLEEPWALKING IN ETERNAL NAP\nBy Lala Luo ('26)\nOn View April 
 3-13 - Rubenstein Gallery 235\nFilm Screening April 4 at 12:00PM - Rubens
 tein Film Theater\nRubenstein Arts Center\n\nMultimedia Installation\n\nM
 y work explores how memories and emotions circulate across physical space
 s\, systems\, and temporalities. I'm drawn to heartache\, nostalgia\, and
  unstable collective realities: feelings that are not entirely one's own\
 , yet deeply felt. I treat fantasy as a structural necessity rather than 
 an escape\, using fiction to explore how subjects know themselves through
  what is missing\, deferred\, or impossible to revisit. Working with movi
 ng images\, installation\, and simulated media\, I fragment and re-stage 
 materials instead of presenting stable narratives. These works hover betw
 een estrangement and sincerity\, using dark humor to frame heartache as a
  way of sensing time out of joint\, and imagining what might have been ot
 herwise.
DURATION:P10D
