CREATED:20260324T194000Z
DESCRIPTION:This session will examine how Constellations and FOCUS courses
  enact the core values of the new curriculum. Panelists Jennifer Hill (Of
 fice of Assessments)\, Jesse Summers (Kenan Institute for Ethics)\, Micha
 el Klien (Dance)\, Minna Ng (Psychology and Neuroscience)\, and Sandra Va
 lnes Quammen (Romance Studies) will discuss how they design courses aroun
 d shared themes that engage multiple disciplinary perspectives\, cultivat
 e curiosity\, and foreground ethical inquiry.\n\nTopics will include:\n\n
 - Structuring courses around compelling\, systemic questions\n- Threading
  ethical challenges and multiple perspectives across a cluster\n- Partner
 ing effectively with first-year writing as an equal contributor to the in
 tellectual arc\n- Creating space for respectful dialogue and intellectual
  risk-taking\n\nParticipants will be invited to share strategies for alig
 ning individual courses with the broader goals of the First-Year Experien
 ce.
DURATION:PT1H
