CREATED:20260331T171637Z
DESCRIPTION:In this colloquium talk\, Dr. McAlpine will discuss his journe
 y from graduate student researcher to co-founder of Allium\, a materials 
 technology startup commercializing stainless clad rebar (SCR).\nAllium is
  taking stainless cladding technology from the world of\nnuclear energy a
 nd applying it at scale to solve the biggest long-term challenge facing r
 einforced concrete infrastructure: rebar\ncorrosion. SCR is a metallic co
 mposite material which combines the corrosion resistance of stainless ste
 el with the mechanical and\nstructural properties of conventional carbon 
 steel reinforcement.\nThis presentation will discuss how Allium's novel l
 aser-based manufacturing technology allows for SCR to be produced with ex
 isting rebar steel mills\, along with real-world infrastructure applicati
 on case studies of SCR including a highway bridge in\nCalifornia and a co
 astal marina in Florida. Finally the sustainability and resilience benefi
 ts of SCR will be outlined including how SCR can enable the broad adoptio
 n of next-generation cementitious\nmaterials and low or zero carbon concr
 ete.
DURATION:PT1H
DTSTAMP:20260331T171637Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260407T120000
LAST-MODIFIED:20260331T171637Z
