CREATED:20260331T171006Z
DESCRIPTION:Join us for the next installment of the Visionary Voices of En
 vironmental Justice community conversation series with Annette Hiatt\, Se
 nior Staff Attorney with the Land Loss Prevention Project. She works with
  small and heritage landowners to retain and preserve the connection of f
 amily to the ownership and retention of land. \n\nVisionary Voices is a c
 onversation series that brings environmental professionals to Duke to sha
 re their career trajectories\, reflections on the intersections of enviro
 nment\, conservation\, and social justice\, and insights for students pre
 paring to enter or influence the environmental field. Our students\, acro
 ss the Nicholas School and the broader Duke community\, deeply value oppo
 rtunities to learn directly from leaders whose work models integrity\, pu
 rpose\, and impact.\nHosted by the CEEJ MEM concentration and co-sponsore
 d by Duke River Center and NSOE Dean's Office. A reception with refreshme
 nts will be held directly after the event.Register at https://duke.zoom.u
 s/meeting/register/OVeV74okRsy4DJI9rUbXJg#/registration to join virtually
 .
