DESCRIPTION:<p>This session explores the complexities of social identity a
 nd how it shapes our experiences\, interactions\, and perspectives. Parti
 cipants will engage in reflective activities to better understand their o
 wn social identities\, recognize the identities of others\, and examine h
 ow bias and group dynamics influence belonging. Participants will leave w
 ith practical strategies to foster inclusion\, build empathy\, and streng
 then connections within the workplace and beyond.&nbsp\;\n\nFacilitated b
 y: <strong>Genevieve Barnes</strong>\, <strong>M.S. M.A</strong>. Assista
 nt Director for Education and Outreach&nbsp\;\n\n <strong>Wednesday\, Apr
 il 8\, 2026 | 9:30 AM - 11:30 AM | </strong><a href="https://duke.kualibu
 ild.com/app/6932fbd0e8d988028a987c3d/run" data-entity-type="external"><st
 rong>REGISTER HERE</strong></a>\n\n    Registrants will receive additiona
 l information about the location\, including parking\, prior to the sessi
 on. Please contact&nbsp\;<a href="mailto:oie-education@duke.edu?subject=O
 IE%20Workshop%20Series">oie-education@duke.edu</a>&nbsp\;if you have any 
 questions or concerns.\n</p>
DURATION:PT2H
