DESCRIPTION:<b>REGISTRATION</b>: <a href="https://forms.office.com/Pages/R
 esponsePage.aspx?id=TsVyyzFKnk2xSh6jbfrJTI9QJhcY12JAolV5CeByrWpUOU1YQzdYW
 E1XVkJMQTg0QTZTSzIyS1UxMC4u" target="_blank">Click Here</a>\n\n<i>NOTE: R
 egistration closes 24 hours before event start. Registrants will receive 
 Zoom information and related materials by email one week and within 24 ho
 urs before the event. </i>\n\nReserve your seat in the <i>Perverse Incent
 ives in Academia</i> RCR Roundtable on April 28th\, 2026 from 10:00-11:30
 am! Join us for a conversation on how perverse incentives are shaping res
 earch culture and what we can do to push back and protect the integrity o
 f our work\n\nThis event is only open to current Duke faculty\, staff\, a
 nd students. Participation in this event fulfills the <b>RCR-200</b> requ
 irement for Faculty and Staff and the <b>714 RCR credit</b> for graduate 
 students. Participants must attend for 60 minutes and participate in brea
 kout room discussion to receive credit.
